<div id="c10">
<p>Hm. I didn&#8217;t really love William Poundstone &#8212; the science was interesting, but I felt like he spent a lot of time proving things that seem obvious (we can&#8217;t make rational decisions), and didn&#8217;t actually illuminate much.</p>

<p>While I was reading it, however, I also read a book called &#8220;I.O.U.: why everyone owes everyone and no one can pay&#8221; by John Lanchester. It&#8217;s a very, very good book, and a good breakdown of the 08 economic disaster. I really recommend it.</p>

